C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ewere%20prevented%20from%20clearing%20a%20homeless%20encampment%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20a%20Ninth%20Circuit%20Court%20of%20Appeals%20rulings%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.ca9.uscourts.gov%2Fdatastore%2Fopinions%2F2019%2F04%2F01%2F15-35845.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMartin%20v.%20Boise%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.ca9.uscourts.gov%2Fdatastore%2Fopinions%2F2022%2F09%2F28%2F20-35752.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJohnson%20v.%20Grants%20Pass%3C%2Fa%3E%20requiring%20local%20governments%20to%20have%20sufficient%20shelter%20beds%20available%20before%20forcing%20unhoused%20people%20off%20the%20streets.%20The%20appeals%20court%20decided%20in%20both%20cases%20that%20removing%20people%20living%20on%20the%20street%20without%20providing%20alternative%20shelter%20violates%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fconstitution.congress.gov%2Fconstitution%2Famendment-8%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEighth%20Amendment's%3C%2Fa%3E%20protections%20against%20cruel%20and%20unusual%20punishment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EState%20and%20federal%20court%20cases%20on%20the%20legality%20of%20clearing%20homeless%20encampments%20reflect%20a%20debate%20between%20some%20governments%20who%20say%20they%20need%20more%20authority%20to%20protect%20public%20safety%20and%20address%20homelessness%2C%20and%20advocates%20who%20argue%20authorities%20are%20exacerbating%20the%20problem%20by%20criminalizing%20homelessness.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20conservatives%20have%20led%20the%20charge%20in%20pushing%20to%20overturn%20the%20Ninth%20Circuit's%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Edecision%2C%20some%20Democrats%2C%20including%20California%20Gov.%20Gavin%20Newsom%2C%20have%20also%20asked%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20to%20overturn%20the%20ruling%2C%20arguing%20that%20it%20makes%20it%20difficult%20or%20impossible%20to%20address%20the%20homelessness%20crisis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCalifornia's%20elected%20officials%20who%20seek%20in%20good%20faith%20to%20improve%20what%20often%20appears%20to%20be%20an%20intractable%20crisis%20have%20found%20themselves%20without%20options%2C%20forced%20to%20abandon%20efforts%20to%20make%20the%20spaces%20occupied%20by%20unhoused%20people%20safer%20for%20those%20within%20and%20near%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Newsom%20administration%20told%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.supremecourt.gov%2FDocketPDF%2F23%2F23-175%2F280288%2F20230922163648635_Amicus%2520Brief%2520for%2520Governor%2520Newsom%2520-%2520Grants%2520Pass_Final.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ein%20an%20amicus%20brief%20last%20year%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPhoenix%2C%20Arizona%2C%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F03%2F19%2Fus%2Fphoenix-businesses-homelessness.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eattracted%20national%20attention%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.azcentral.com%2Fstory%2Fnews%2Flocal%2Fphoenix%2F2022%2F08%2F11%2Fphoenix-residents-sue-city-over-states-largest-homeless-encampment%2F10296261002%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ea%20contentious%20legal%20battle%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20over%20a%20downtown%20homeless%20encampment%20of%201%2C000%20people%20called%20%26quot%3BThe%20Zone.%26quot%3B%20Local%20residents%20and%20business%20owners%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fox10phoenix.com%2Fnews%2Farizona-court-rules-that-city-of-phoenix-must-keep-the-zone-free-of-the-homeless%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ealleged%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20city%20allowed%20the%20encampment%20to%20become%20a%20public%20nuisance%20and%20even%20a%20danger.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20a%20Maricopa%20County%20judge%20ordered%20Phoenix%20officials%20to%20clear%20the%20Zone.%20The%20city%20responded%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F05%2F10%2Fus%2Fphoenix-homeless-camp-the-zone.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ethreatening%20citation%20or%20arrest%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20those%20who%20refused%20to%20leave%20the%20street.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F12%2F26%2Fus%2Fphoenix-homeless-encampment-zone.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EIt%20also%20built%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20hundreds%20of%20new%20temporary%20shelter%20beds%2C%20some%20longer-term%20housing%2C%20and%20an%20authorized%20outdoor%20camping%20area.%20But%20the%20crisis%20is%20far%20from%20over.%20As%20home%20prices%20have%20risen%20in%20Phoenix%2C%20the%20county's%20homeless%20population%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fktar.com%2Fstory%2F5505669%2Fwithout-a-home-roots-of-metro-phoenix-homelessness-problem-run-deep%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520number%2520of%2520people%2520experiencing%2C(MAG)%2520once%2520a%2520year.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehas%20grown%20by%2070%20percent%20since%202017%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20city%20of%20Phoenix%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.supremecourt.gov%2FDocketPDF%2F23%2F23-175%2F280385%2F20230925144546598_City%2520of%2520Phoenix%2520Amicus%2520Brief%25209-22-23%2520FINAL%2520Version.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efiled%20an%20amicus%20brief%3C%2Fa%3E%20supporting%20Grants%20Pass'%20effort%20to%20overturn%20the%20appeals%20court%20ruling%2C%20arguing%20that%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Ethe%20Ninth%20Circuit%20%26quot%3Bstrayed%20far%20from%20the%20historical%20origins%20of%20the%20Eighth%20Amendment.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLike%20so%20many%20other%20cities%20confronting%20the%20homelessness%20crisis%2C%20conflicting%20court%20decisions%20have%20hampered%20Phoenix's%20ability%20to%20tread%20forward%20confidently%20on%20a%20clear%20approach%E2%80%94and%20solution%E2%80%94to%20this%20growing%20challenge%2C%26quot%3B%20Phoenix%20Mayor%20Kate%20Gallego%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20to%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BI%20hope%20that%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20can%20deliver%20clarity%20to%20cities%20so%20that%20we%20can%20focus%20completely%20on%20ending%20people's%20homelessness%20rather%20than%20on%20navigating%20a%20web%20of%20disparate%20legal%20arguments.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20dangers%20of%20criminalizing%20homelessness%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAdvocates%20for%20the%20homeless%20argue%20that%20the%20Ninth%20Circuit%20decision%20doesn't%20prevent%20local%20governments%20from%20enforcing%20all%20kinds%20of%20laws%20protecting%20public%20safety%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20homeless%20encampments.%20It%20simply%20prevents%20them%20from%20criminalizing%20those%20who%20have%20nowhere%20else%20to%20go.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJeffrey%20Selbin%2C%20a%20law%20professor%20at%20UC%20Berkeley%20and%20director%20of%20the%20Policy%20Advocacy%20Clinic%2C%20said%20public%20officials'%20complaints%20that%20their%20hands%20are%20tied%20are%20overblown.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20spite%20of%20politicians'%20claims%20to%20the%20contrary%2C%20the%20vast%20array%20of%20public%20health%20and%20safety%20laws%20are%20untouched%20by%20the%20rulings%2C%26quot%3B%20Selbin%20said.%20%26quot%3BLocal%20officials%20can%20still%20cite%2C%20arrest%2C%20and%20prosecute%20people%20for%20any%20other%20violation%20of%20the%20law%2C%20including%20for%20all%20crimes%20against%20people%20and%20property.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHomeless%20advocates%20say%20that%20criminalizing%20homelessness%20promotes%20a%20vicious%20cycle%20that%20only%20makes%20it%20harder%20for%20people%20to%20find%20homes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20are%20living%20outside%20and%20are%20impoverished%2C%20a%20ticket%20or%20a%20fee%20is%20probably%20something%20you%20can't%20afford%2C%20and%20then%20you%20have%20unpaid%20tickets%2C%20which%20impacts%20your%20credit%20rating%2C%20which%20makes%20it%20harder%20to%20find%20a%20place%20to%20live%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Jesse%20Rabinowitz%2C%20a%20campaign%20and%20communications%20director%20at%20the%20National%20Homelessness%20Law%20Center.%20%26quot%3BOr%20you%20