rito%20season%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%20And%20once%20again%2C%20the%20people%20are%20asking%3A%20%26quot%3BWhat%20the%20hell%20is%20burrito%20season%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20week%2C%20in%20sharp%20contrast%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flayoffs-sweeping-us-these-are-companies-making-cuts-2024%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eugly%20layoff%20news%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20coming%20out%20of%20other%20big%20companies%2C%20Chipotle%20announced%20that%20it's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchipotle-student-loan-payoff-perk-targets-gen-z-workers-hiring-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Elooking%20to%20hire%2019%2C000%20workers%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20over%20the%20next%20month.%20The%20reason%3F%20According%20to%20the%20fast-casual%20chain%2C%20it's%20preparing%20for%20an%20annual%20surge%20in%20cylindrical%20Mexican%20food%20consumption%20that%20lasts%20from%20March%20through%20May.%20Burrito%20season%2C%20the%20company%20says%2C%20represents%20its%20busiest%20time%20of%20the%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20like%20me%2C%20you%20may%20find%20yourself%20scratching%20your%20head%20at%20this%20one.%20Does%20everybody%20wake%20up%20on%20March%201%20and%20suddenly%20feel%20a%20deep%20urge%20to%20seek%20out%20overpriced%20guacamole%3F%20Does%20the%20return%20of%20spring%20cause%20an%20irresistible%20desire%20for%20rice%20and%20beans%3F%20And%20why%20do%20Americans%20suddenly%20turn%20against%20Mexican%20food%20in%20June%3F%20Is%20it%20simply%20too%20hot%3F%20Burnout%20from%20Cinco%20de%20Mayo%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20asked%20a%20spokesperson%20for%20Chipotle%20to%20shed%20some%20light%20on%20the%20mysteries%20of%20burrito%20season%2C%20her%20answer%20was%20both%20straightforward%20and%20perplexing.%20Chipotle%20sees%20its%20highest%20sales%20volume%20in%20the%20spring%2C%20she%20said%2C%20thanks%20to%20%26quot%3Bweather%20and%20daylight.%26quot%3B%20The%20days%20are%20warmer%20and%20the%20sun%20is%20out%20longer%2C%20so%20people%20apparently%20want%20to%20chow%20down%20on%20burritos.%20Square%2C%20the%20company%20that%20provides%20restaurants%20with%20those%20little%20white%20card%20readers%2C%20confirmed%20for%20me%20that%20from%20March%20through%20May%20last%20year%2C%20it%20saw%20a%2020%25%20increase%20in%20burrito%20sales%20at%20the%20locations%20using%20its%20tech%20compared%20with%20the%20three%20months%20prior.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20all%20makes%20sense%2C%20I%20suppose.%20But%20after%20confirming%20the%20existence%20of%20burrito%20season%2C%20I%20was%20still%20left%20with%20two%20big%20questions.%20Does%20the%20phenomenon%20apply%20solely%20to%20burritos%3F%20And%20why%20does%20it%20suddenly%20stop%20in%20June%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20turns%20out%20that%20burritos%20aren't%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20the%20only%20craving%20people%20get%20as%20the%20flowers%20start%20to%20bloom.%20%26quot%3BThe%20warmer%20spring%20weather%20encourages%20more%20people%20to%20dine%20out%2C%20increasing%20foot%20traffic%20to%20restaurants%2C%26quot%3B%20Siye%20Desta%2C%20an%20equity%20analyst%20at%20CFRA%20Research%2C%20told%20me.%20Warmer%20weather%20also%20brings%20more%20social%20activities%2C%20he%20added%2C%20which%20means%20people%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20dine%20out%20in%20groups%20or%20place%20catering%20orders%20for%20events.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESquare%20also%20told%20me%20that%20it%20saw%20a%20similar%20sales%20jump%20for%20other%20food%20items%2C%20like%20burgers%20and%20sushi%2C%20and%20data%20from%20the%20Census%20Bureau%20confirms%20a%20broad%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.census.gov%2Fecon%2Fcurrentdata%2F%3FprogramCode%3DMARTS%26startYear%3D2014%26endYear%3D2024%26categories%5B%5D%3D722%26dataType%3DSM%26geoLevel%3DUS%26adjusted%3D0%26notAdjusted%3D1%26errorData%3D0%23line083%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eseasonal%20uptick%20in%20eating%20out%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Sales%20at%20restaurants%20and%20bars%20seem%20to%20especially%20suck%20in%20February%20%E2%80%94%20arguably%20winter's%20bleakest%20month%20%E2%80%94%20and%20then%20start%20to%20pick%20up%20in%20March.%20Data%20from%20the%20Bureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics%20also%20shows%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdata.bls.gov%2FPDQWeb%2Fjt%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ehiring%20in%20accommodation%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20food%20services%20picks%20up%20in%20the%20spring.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20spring%20spending%20boom%20isn't%20even%20just%20a%20restaurant%20thing.%20Nicer%20weather%20means%20people%20open%20their%20wallets%20more%20for%20%3Cem%3Eeverything%3C%2Fem%3E.%20And%20it%20has%20more%20to%20do%20with%20light%20than%20temperature.%20%26quot%3BWe%20looked%20at%20a%20bunch%20of%20different%20types%20of%20weather%20%E2%80%94%20rain%20or%20snow%2C%20hot%20and%20cold%20%E2%80%94%20but%20what%20really%20mattered%20was%20sunlight%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Kyle%20Murray%2C%20a%20business%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Alberta%20who%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ualberta.ca%2Fbusiness%2Fmedia-library%2Fcentres%2Fsor%2Fdocuments%2Fmurrayetal2010-theeffectofweatheronconsumerspending.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Estudied%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20weather%20effects%20on%20consumer%20spending.%20%26quot%3BAs%20you%20get%20more%20sunlight%20on%20a%20particular%20day%20or%20week%2C%20people's%20negative%20emotions%20start%20to%20decrease%2C%20and%20they%20start%20to%20spend%20more%20money.%26quot%3B%20When%20the%20sun%20comes%20out%2C%20we%20cheer%20up.%20And%20when%20Americans%20are%20happy%2C%20we%20whip%20out%20our%20credit%20cards.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhich%20brings%20me%20to%20my%20second%20question%3A%20Wouldn't%20the%20spending%20spree%20apply%20to%20the%20summer%20months%20too%3F%20Why%20does%20Memorial%20Day%20mark%20the%20end%20of%20the%20burrito%20bonanza%3F%20When%20I%20asked%20Chipotle%20why%20burrito%20season%20cut%20off%20in%20June%2C%20the%20spokesperson%20said%20its%20restaurants%20near%20colleges%20and%20universities%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nrn.com%2Ffast-casual%2Fwhy-chipotle-focused-small-and-college-towns%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eof%20which%20there%20are%20many%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20did%20more%20business%20during%20the%20academic%20year.%20Fewer%20students%20after%20May%20means%20fewer%20burritos%20at%20Chipotle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECensus%20Bureau%20data%20shows%20sales%20at%20food%20services%20and%20drinking%20places%20do%20tend%20to%20dip%20slightly%20in%20June%2C%20though%20sales%20generally%20perk%20up%20for%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20summer.%20That%20would%20seem%20to%20indicate%20that%20any%20summer%20slump%20may%20be%20more%20burrito-specific.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJustin%20Seitzler%2C%20the%20director%20of%20operations%20at%20El%20Gallo%20Taqueria%2C%20a%20taqueria%20with%20four%20locations%20in%20New%20York%2C%20shed%20some%20extra%20light%20on%20why%20burrito%20season%20tapered%20off%20come%20summer.%20After%20February%2C%20he%20said%2C%20business%20starts%20to%20pick%20up%20until%20%26quot%3Bthe%20dog%20days%20of%20summer%2C%26quot%3B%20July%20and%20August.%20At%20that%20point%2C%20folks%20head%20off%20on%20vacation.%20%26quot%3BNew%20Yorkers%20tend%20to%20hit%20the%20Hamptons%20on%20the%20weekend%2C%20or%20they'll%20go%20find%20a%20beach%2C%26quot%3B%20Seitzler%20said.%20%26quot%3BEveryone%20leaves%20town.%26quot%3B%20Once%20school%20starts%2C%20business%20starts%20to%20pick%20up%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20everything%20there%20is%20a%20season%2C%20and%20evidently%2C%20from%20March%20to%20May%2C%20that%20season%20is%20for%20rice%2C%20beans%2C%20and%20cheese%20in%20a%20tortilla.%20So%20even%20if%20you're%20not%20in%20the%20mood%20for%20a%20burrito%20right%20now%2C%20don't%20be%20surprised%20if%20you%20are%20in%20about%20six%20weeks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Femily-ste