w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F04%2F20115409%2Funnamed.jpg%20526w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-649461%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22363%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EIllustration%3A%20Pariplab%20Chakraborty%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMuseums%20in%20the%20West%20are%20stuffed%20full%20of%20artefacts%20that%20were%20seized%2C%20looted%20or%20sold%20under%20duress.%20If%20it%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20for%20the%20legacy%20of%20the%20Empire%2C%20some%20of%20Britain%E2%80%99s%20main%20museums%20would%20be%20bare.%20Tristram%20Hunt%2C%20the%20director%20of%20the%20Victoria%20and%20Albert%20Museum%20in%20London%2C%20says%20the%20British%20military%20ransacking%20of%20Kumasi%20in%201874%2C%20during%20which%20the%20gold%20was%20taken%2C%20%E2%80%98stands%20as%20one%20of%20the%20most%20infamous%20episodes%20in%20the%20history%20of%20British%20colonial%20plunder%E2%80%99.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20decision%20to%20send%20some%20of%20the%20gold%20back%20to%20Ghana%2C%20Hunt%20insists%2C%20%E2%80%98is%20not%20about%20reparative%20justice%20for%20the%20colonial%20past%E2%80%99%20but%20that%E2%80%99s%20how%20many%20around%20the%20world%20may%20see%20it.%20And%20it%20will%20fuel%20the%20debate%20about%20how%20much%20of%20the%20spoils%20of%20the%20Empire%20and%20war%20should%20be%20given%20back%3A%20the%20Elgin%20marbles%2C%20part%20of%20the%20Parthenon%20sculptures%2C%20could%20soon%20be%20on%20display%20in%20Athens%3B%20some%20Benin%20bronzes%20in%20British%20museums%20are%20being%20returned%20to%20Nigeria%3B%20should%20all%20museum%20items%20acquired%20in%20questionable%20circumstances%20be%20sent%20back%20to%20the%20country%20of%20origin%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESad%20to%20say%2C%20loot%20and%20plunder%20have%20been%20part%20of%20military%20conquest%20across%20the%20world%20and%20through%20the%20centuries.%20The%20word%20%E2%80%98loot%E2%80%99%20is%20derived%20from%20Hindi%20and%2C%20it%20seems%2C%20developed%20during%20the%20early%20part%20of%20British%20military%20expansion%20in%20India.%20While%20deriving%20booty%20from%20war%20is%20ages%20old%2C%20Western%20imperialism%20brought%20plunder%20%E2%80%93%20of%20wealth%2C%20fine%20arts%2C%20sacred%20items%20and%20cultural%20heirlooms%20%E2%80%93%20to%20a%20new%20level.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EGarnet%20Wolseley%2C%20the%20British%20general%20who%20led%20the%20punitive%20expedition%20against%20the%20Asante%20king%2C%20had%20form%20when%20it%20came%20to%20serving%20the%20Empire.%20In%20his%2020s%2C%20he%20fought%20at%20Lucknow%20during%20the%201857%20Rebellion%20%E2%80%93%20and%20was%20contemptuous%20of%20the%20people%20the%20British%20colonised.%20His%20burning%20of%20Kumasi%20and%20seizing%20of%20the%20Asante%20gold%20was%20seen%20in%20Britain%20at%20the%20time%20as%20an%20act%20of%20heroism%3A%20he%20was%20promoted%2C%20received%20the%20formal%20thanks%20of%20both%20houses%20of%20Parliament%20and%20was%20awarded%20a%20grant%20of%20%C2%A325%2C000%20(a%20staggering%20amount%20and%20the%20equivalent%20today%20of%20%C2%A33.5%20million%20or%20Rs%2035%20crore).%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20gold%20items%20seized%2C%20and%20now%20being%20returned%2C%20include%20a%20sword%20of%20state%20and%20a%20ceremonial%20pipe%2C%20as%20well%20as%20badges%20worn%20by%20members%20of%20the%20ruler%E2%80%99s%20entourage%20responsible%20for%20%E2%80%98washing%E2%80%99%20the%20soul%20of%20the%20king.%20There%20were%20not%20simply%20exceptional%20pieces%20of%20craftsmanship%2C%20but%20items%20which%20represented%20the%20authority%20of%20the%20ruler%20%E2%80%93%20the%20Asantehene.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETristram%20Hunt%20has%20described%20the%20items%20as%20the%20Asante%20equivalent%20of%20Britain%E2%80%99s%20crown%20jewels%20and%20believes%20their%20return%20represents%20%E2%80%98a%20new%20spirit%20of%20partnership%20and%20cultural%20exchange%E2%80%99.%20Nana%20Oforiatta%20Ayim%2C%20a%20Ghanaian%20cultural%20expert%2C%20said%20it%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98a%20sign%20of%20some%20kind%20of%20healing%20and%20commemoration%20for%20the%20violence%20that%20happened%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20agreement%20about%20the%20return%20has%20been%20made%20not%20with%20the%20Ghanaian%20government%20but%20with%20the%20current%20Asantehene%2C%20Otumfo%20Osei%20Tutu%20II%2C%20and%20the%20gold%20will%20be%20displayed%20at%20the%20palace%20museum%20in%20Kumasi.%20But%20the%20items%20are%20not%20simply%20being%20handed%20back%20to%20the%20Asante%20royal%20family.%20They%20are%20being%20given%C2%A0%20%2C%20initially%20of%20three%20years.%20This%20has%20angered%20many%20heritage%20experts%20in%20Africa%2C%20who%20say%20it%E2%80%99s%20disgraceful%20that%20Britain%20should%20lend%20back%20items%20its%20army%20looted%20rather%20than%20making%20an%20act%20of%20unqualified%20restitution.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20museum%20directors%20in%20London%20are%20constrained%20by%20legislation%20which%20outlaws%20the%20big%20museums%20from%20giving%20away%20or%20selling%20any%20of%20their%20principal%20holdings.%20That%20law%20could%20be%20changed%2C%20of%20course%2C%20but%20there%20is%20no%20early%20prospect%20of%20new%20legislation.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESome%20British%20commentators%20justify%20the%20plunder%20on%20display%20in%20British%20museum%20by%20arguing%20that%20it%20is%20kept%20well%2C%20properly%20conserved%20and%20can%20be%20seen%20by%20millions%20of%20visitors%20from%20around%20the%20world%20who%20come%20to%20London%20every%20year.%20But%20the%20tide%20is%20running%20in%20the%20opposite%20direction.%20It%E2%80%99s%20likely%20that%20many%20more%20heritage%20items%20will%20return%20home%20to%20be%20displayed%20in%20the%20countries%2C%20and%20amid%20the%20cultures%2C%20in%20which%20they%20were%20created.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20just%20in%20case%20you%20are%20wondering%2C%20don%E2%80%99t%20expect%20the%20%3Cem%3EKoh-i-Noor%3C%2Fem%3E%20to%20be%20heading%20back.%20It%E2%80%99s%20not%20simply%20that%20this%20spectacular%20diamond%20is%20now%20part%20of%20Britain%E2%80%99s%20crown%20jewels%2C%20nor%20that%20there%E2%80%99s%20no%20real%20clarity%20about%20whether%20Britain%20stole%20the%20stone.%20There%20are%20three%20nations%20%E2%80%93%20Pakistan%20and%20Afghanistan%20and%20India%20%E2%80%93%20that%20claim%20the%20Koh-i-Noor%2C%20so%20the%20diplomatic%20complications%20of%20any%20restitution%20would%20be%20too%20daunting.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Ffrino%5C%22%3EAndrew%20Whitehead%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0is%20an%20honorary%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Nottingham%20in%20the%20UK%20and%20a%20former%20BBC%20India%20correspondent.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cstrong%3ELondon%20Calling%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0How%20does%20India%20look%20from%20afar%3F%20Looming%20world%20power%20or%20dysfunctional%20democracy%3F%20And%20what%E2%80%99s%20happening%20in%20Britain%2C%20and%20the%20West%2C%20that%20India%20needs%20to%20know%20about%20and%20perhaps%20learn%20from%3F%20This%20fortnightly%20column%20helps%20forge%20the%20connections%20so%20essential%20in%20our%20globalising%20world.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706687887000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F31125920%2FGEsp5toXUAAKAUv.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fghanas-stolen-crown-jewels-are-going-home-but-only-for-3-years%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Exactly%20150%20years%20after%20they%20were%20plundered%20by%20a%20British%20military%20expedition%2C%20more%20than%2030%20exquisite%20pieces%20of%20Asante%20gold%20held%20by%20the%20British%20Museum%20and%20the%20Victoria%20and%20Albert%20Museum%20are%20being%20returned%20to%20Ghana%20on%20a%20'long-term%20loan'.%22