0J%26amp%3BK%3A%20SC%20Pulls%20Up%20Centre%2C%20Says%20'Review%20Orders%20Not%20Meant%20to%20Be%20Kept%20in%20Cupboard'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F01%2F24110414%2FScreenshot-2022-01-24-at-11.04.08-AM.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20pulled%20up%20the%20Union%20government%20noting%20that%20review%20orders%20of%20the%20special%20committee%20constituted%20in%20May%202020%20on%20the%20restoration%20of%20the%20internet%20in%20the%20Union%20territory%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20must%20be%20published.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20division%20Bench%20of%20Justice%20B.R.%20Gavai%20and%20Justice%20Sanjay%20Karol%20told%20the%20government%20the%20review%20orders%20of%20the%20committee%20are%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Findia%2Finternet-restrictions-in-jk-review-orders-not-meant-to-be-kept-in-cupboard-says-sc-9135692%2F%5C%22%3Enot%20meant%20to%20be%20kept%20in%20a%20cupboard%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%20but%20must%20be%20published.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERuling%20in%20May%202020%20in%20a%20case%20pertaining%20to%20internet%20restrictions%20in%20the%20Union%20territory%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20had%20directed%20the%20Centre%20to%20set%20up%20the%20said%20special%20committee%20to%20assess%20the%20necessity%20of%20the%20restrictions%20on%20the%20internet%20in%20J%26amp%3BK.%20The%20court%20had%20suggested%20that%20the%20committee%20comprise%20the%20secretary%20of%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Home%20Affairs%2C%20secretary%20of%20the%20Department%20of%20Communication%2C%20and%20the%20chief%20secretary%20of%20the%20Union%20territory%20as%20its%20members.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Centre%20began%20putting%20restrictions%20on%20the%20internet%20in%20the%20J%26amp%3BK%20in%20August%202019%20with%20the%20abrogation%20of%20Article%20370%20and%20the%20downgrading%20of%20the%20statehood%20status.%20Journalist%20Anuradha%20Bhasin%20moved%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20January%202020%20calling%20for%20the%20review%20of%20the%20restrictions%20placed%20on%20the%20internet.%20Not%20only%20did%20the%20court%20agree%20with%20Bhasin%E2%80%99s%20contention%20in%20January%202020%20but%20it%20also%20directed%20the%20setting%20up%20of%20the%20said%20committee.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Findia%2Finternet-restrictions-in-jk-review-orders-not-meant-to-be-kept-in-cupboard-says-sc-9135692%2F%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Indian%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20May%202020%20order%20had%20directed%20the%20Union%20home%20secretary%20to%20%E2%80%9Cimmediately%20determine%20the%20necessity%20of%20the%20continuation%20of%20limiting%20mobile%20internet%20to%202G%20speed%20in%20the%20region%E2%80%A6%20and%20allowing%20faster%20internet%20(3G%20or%204G)%20on%20a%20trial%20basis%20in%20certain%20geographical%20areas%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAgainst%20this%20backdrop%2C%20advocate%20Shadan%20Farasat%20on%20Tuesday%2C%20January%2030%2C%20appearing%20for%20the%20Foundation%20for%20Media%20Professionals%2C%20told%20the%20court%20that%20according%20to%20the%20%3Cem%3EAnuradha%20Bhasin%3C%2Fem%3E%20judgment%20and%20the%20Indian%20Telegraph%20Act%2C%20the%20administration%20is%20required%20to%20publish%20the%20review%20orders%20and%20the%20mother%20order%20on%20internet%20restrictions%20in%20the%20Union%20territory.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20this%2C%20additional%20solicitor%20general%20K.M.%20Nataraj%2C%20appearing%20for%20the%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20administration%2C%20said%2C%E2%80%9D%20We%20have%20complied%20with%20all%20the%20prayers%20made%20in%20earlier%20petitions.%20A%20contempt%20petition%20was%20also%20filed%20and%20was%20dismissed.%20Now%2C%20they%20have%20come%20up%20with%20a%20new%20prayer%20for%20publication%20of%20recommendations%20and%20deliberations%20of%20the%20special%20committee.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20this%20stage%2C%20the%20court%20in%20response%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CIt%20may%20not%20be%20necessary%20to%20publish%20the%20deliberations%20(of%20the%20committee)%2C%20but%20the%20review%20orders%20passed%20are%20required%20to%20be%20published.%20Review%20orders%20are%20not%20meant%20to%20be%20kept%20in%20the%20cupboard.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20gave%20the%20J%26amp%3BK%20administration%20two%20weeks%20time%20to%20additional%20solictor%20general%20to%20take%20instructions%20from%20the%20authorities%20concerned.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20applicant%20has%20submitted%20that%20though%20this%20court%20in%20the%20case%20of%20Anuradha%20Bhasin%20held%20that%20even%20review%20orders%20must%20be%20published%2C%20the%20same%20is%20not%20being%20done.%20ASG%20KM%20Nataraj%20has%20said%20that%20a%20perusal%20of%20the%20order%20would%20show%20that%20deliberations%20are%20not%20required%20to%20be%20published.%20We%20are%20prima%20facie%20of%20the%20view%20that%20it%20may%20not%20be%20necessary%20to%20publish%20the%20deliberations%2C%20but%20the%20orders%20passed%20in%20the%20review%20required%20to%20be%20published.%20Mr%20Nataraj%20seeks%20two%20weeks%E2%80%99%20time%20to%20take%20instructions%20in%20this%20regard%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20court%20ruled%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fsupreme-court-jammu-and-kashmir-internet-shutdowns-review-committee-orders-248016%3Finfinitescroll%3D1%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20%3Cem%3ELivelaw.in%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706682300000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F01%2F24110414%2FScreenshot-2022-01-24-at-11.04.08-AM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Finternet-curbs-in-jk-sc-pulls-up-centre-says-review-orders-not-meant-to-be-kept-in-cupboard%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20top%20court%20directed%20the%20Centre%20to%20publish%20the%20review%20orders%20of%20the%20special%20committee%2