king%2C%20accountability%20seeking%20institution.%20It%20is%20struggling%20to%20properly%20do%20any%20of%20these%20things.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20what%20and%20who%20is%20stopping%20Parliament%20from%20rising%20to%20its%20constitutional%20role%3F%20Primarily%20the%20government%2C%20but%20also%2C%20we%20the%20people%20of%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EGovernment%20decimates%20the%20dignity%20of%20Parliament%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20eve%20of%20the%20last%20Parliament%20session%20of%20the%20current%20government%2C%20I%20posted%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2F_maadhyam_%2Fstatus%2F1752204125838950452%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3Ethread%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20platform%20%E2%80%98X%E2%80%99%20(formerly%20Twitter)%20about%20the%20%E2%80%98wrongs%E2%80%99%20committed%20by%20the%20government%20during%20its%20term.%20The%20list%20of%20%E2%80%98wrongs%E2%80%99%20mentioned%20in%20this%20thread%20are%20by%20no%20means%20exhaustive%20but%20they%20are%20glaring%20enough%20to%20make%20any%20concerned%20citizen%20worry.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20outset%20is%20the%20matter%20of%20the%20vacant%20post%20of%20deputy%20speaker%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha.%20Article%2093%20of%20the%20Constitution%2C%20in%20very%20clear%20terms%2C%20mandates%20having%20a%20deputy%20speaker%20as%20soon%20as%20possible.%20It%E2%80%99s%20been%20more%20than%20four%20years%20now.%20It%20is%20immaterial%20for%20the%20government%20to%20argue%20that%20the%20House%20can%20function%20without%20a%20deputy%20speaker%2C%20who%20is%20conventionally%20a%20nominee%20of%20the%20opposition.%20What%20is%20of%20absolute%20concern%20is%20the%20cavalier%20attitude%20of%20the%20government%20towards%20a%20constitutional%20mandate.%20Why%3F%20Because%20it%20believes%20that%20it%20can%20get%20away%20with%20it.%20And%20we%20are%20letting%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThen%20comes%20the%20very%20important%20issue%20of%20fewer%20and%20shorter%20Parliament%20sessions.%20Nothing%20can%20indicate%20government%E2%80%99s%20contempt%20for%20Parliament%20more%20than%20this.%20This%20is%20because%20the%20government%20has%20been%20empowered%20to%20decide%20when%20to%20convene%20a%20session%20and%20for%20how%20long.%20Dr%20B.R.%20Ambedkar%2C%20while%20speaking%20in%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%2C%20expressed%20confidence%20that%20in%20independent%20India%2C%20there%20will%20be%20no%20occasion%20for%20the%20executive%20to%20shun%20or%20show%20a%20callous%20conduct%20towards%20the%20legislature.%20Unfortunately%2C%20he%20has%20been%20proved%20wrong.%20A%20Parliament%20session%20is%20convened%20not%20as%20a%20matter%20of%20answerability%20towards%20the%20legislature%20but%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20calculations%20of%20political%20exigencies.%20There%20are%20crucial%20state%20assembly%20elections%2C%20Parliament%20session%20can%20wait.%20There%20is%20Covid%2C%20why%20do%20we%20need%20Parliament%20to%20question%20the%20government%20during%20a%20pandemic%20anyway%2C%20keep%20it%20closed%20for%20as%20long%20as%20possible.%20As%20I%20argued%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.epw.in%2Fjournal%2F2020%2F24%2Fcommentary%2Fparliaments-time-pandemic.html%5C%22%3Eelsewhere%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20functional%20Parliament%20was%20more%20crucial%20than%20ever%20during%20the%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShorter%20and%20fewer%20sessions%20also%20mean%20that%20the%20time%20of%20Parliament%20is%20prioritised%20to%20focus%20on%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20agenda.%20If%20there%20is%20less%20time%2C%20all%20other%20business%20will%20be%20sacrificed%20so%20that%20Bills%20can%20be%20cleared.%20Any%20demand%20for%20debate%20from%20the%20opposition%20will%20be%20accommodated%20only%20if%20it%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20disturb%20government%E2%80%99s%20agenda%20for%20a%20particular%20session.%20And%20if%20the%20opposition%20protests%20because%20its%20demands%20are%20not%20being%20met%2C%20the%20%E2%80%98time%20lost%E2%80%99%20due%20to%20disruptions%20is%20compensated%20by%20pushing%20Bills%20through%20without%20debate.%20Perhaps%2C%20it%20is%20the%20fear%20of%20losing%20time%20which%20also%20prevents%20government%20from%20sending%20Bills%20to%20Parliament%20Committees%20for%20scrutiny%2C%20analysis%20and%20public%20consultations.%20Shorter%20and%20fewer%20sessions%20also%20provide%20a%20fertile%20ground%20to%20govern%20by%20issuing%20Ordinances%2C%20through%20which%20parliamentary%20law-making%20process%20is%20bypassed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20finally%2C%20there%20is%20the%20crucial%20issue%20of%20answering%20parliament%20questions.%20The%20government%E2%80%99s%20discomfort%20with%20questions%20is%20understandable%2C%20yet%20peculiar.%20It%20can%20go%20to%20great%20lengths%20to%20avoid%20answering%20questions%2C%20even%20getting%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fat-least-three-critical-flaws-in-the-ethics-committee-report-on-mahua-moitra%5C%22%3Eopposition%20MP%20expelled%3C%2Fa%3E!%20It%20has%20been%20resorting%20to%20the%20dubious%20practice%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fcost-of-suspending-members-of-parliament%5C%22%3Edeleting%20questions%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20opposition%20MPs%20who%20are%20suspended.%20When%20it%20has%20no%20option%20left%20but%20to%20answer%2C%20it%20simply%20evades%20or%20ignores%20questions%2C%20provides%20misleading%20or%20incomplete%20answers%2C%20and%20when%20all%20else%20fails%2C%20says%20that%20data%20isn%E2%80%99t%20available.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20biggest%20disservice%20that%20the%20government%20has%20done%20is%20making%20Parliament%20redundant%20in%20people%E2%80%99s%20imaginations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPeople%20abandon%20the%20Parliament%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20posted%20about%20the%20%E2%80%98wrongs%E2%80%99%20being%20done%20by%20the%20government%2C%20there%20were%20many%20who%20disagreed.%20Though%20disagreement%20and%20dissent%20are%20fundamental%20to%20a%20democracy%2C%20it%20is%20important%20to%20address%20several%20fallacies%20in%20their%20arguments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20citizen%20argued%20that%20government%20is%20being%20criticised%20for%20getting%20work%20done.%20Apparently%20getting%20many%20Bills%20pushed%20through%20Parliament%2C%20whether%20or%20not%20proper%20debate%2C%20deliberation%20and%20scrutiny%20happened%20for%20each%2C%20is%20a%20sign%20of%20a%20government%20which%20means%20business.%20It%20is%20not%20uncommon%20for%20even%20media%20to%20declare%20a%20Parliament%20session%20as%20%E2%80%98productive%E2%80%99%20if%20a%20large%20number%20of%20Bills%20are%20pushed%20through%20in%20a%20short%20time.%20However%2C%20Parliament%20is%20not%20a%20Bill%20making%20factory.%20Number%20of%20Bills%20passed%20in%20a%20session%20is%20not%20a%20measure%20of%20Parliament%E2%80%99s%20efficiency.%20Law%20making%20by%20Parliament%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20mean%20rubber%20stamping%20every%20proposal%20put%20before%20it%20by%20the%20government.%20On%20the%20contrary%2C%20law%20making%20is%20a%20deliberately%20slow%20process%2C%20requiring%20multiple%20readings%2C%20deeper%20debates%20within%20committees%20and%20plenary%20debates%20in%20Parliament.%20That%20is%20what%20the%20rules%20and%20procedures%20also%20provide%20for.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20idea%20is%20for%20every%20possible%20input%20from%20as%20many%20stakeholders%20to%20inform%20law%20making.%20Because%20law%20making%20is%20a%20costly%20process.%20There%20is%20the%20cost%20of%20making%20a%20law%2C%20and%20the%20cost%20of%20implementing%20a%20law.%20Not%20just%20a%20monetary%20cost%20to%20the%20taxpayers%2C%20but%20there%20can%20be%20human%2C%20social%2C%20environmental%20costs%20associated%20as%20well.%20Bad%20laws%20can%20violate%20rights%20of%20people%2C%20can%20lead%20to%20protests%20and%20unrest%20in%20a%20society.%20This%20is%20why%20different%20stakeholders%20and%20their%20representatives%20must%20be%20involved%20in%20law%20making%20process.%20This%20is%20deliberative%20democracy%20in%20practice.%20Pushing%20bills%20through%20without%20any%20debate%2C%20or%20amid%20protests%2C%20or%20in%20absence%20of%20different%20voices%2C%20is%20undemocratic.%20As%20I%20had%20argued%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fthe-illegal-ways-of-law-making-by-indias-parliament%5C%22%3Eprevious%20article%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20passing%20bills%20in%20this%20manner%20can%20be%20held%20to%20be%20%E2%80%99illegal%E2%80%99%20and%20unconstitutional.%20There%20is%20just%20no%20justification%20for%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20citizen%20argued%20that%20shorter%20Parliament%20sessions%20are%20not%20problematic%20because%20anyway%20the%20opposition%20uses%20the%20sessions%20to%20protest%20on%20various%20issues%20and%20disrupt.%20Several%20citizens%20questioned%20the%20conduct%20of%20the%20opposition.%20Here%2C%20it%20is%20important%20to%20recall%20the%20basics.%20It%20is%20not%20just%20the%20government%20which%20has%20a%20%E2%80%98mandate%E2%80%99%20to%20govern%2C%20every%20Member%20of%20Parliament%2C%20including%20from%20the%20opposition%20has%20the%20%E2%80%98mandate%E2%80%99%20to%20represent%20their%20constituents%2C%20contribute%20to%20law%20making%20and%20keep%20the%20government%20under%20check.%20We%20vote%20for%20who%20we%20want%20as%20our%20Member%20of%20Parliament%2C%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20directly%20vote%20for%20who%20our%20ministers%20or%20prime%20minister%20will%20be.%20Therefore%2C%20the%20prime%20minister%20and%20her%20cabinet%20of%20ministers%20are%20answerable%20to%20us%20through%20our%20MPs.%20And%20thus%2C%20the%20role%20of%20each%20MP%20and%20particularly%20the%20opposition%20becomes%20crucial.%20The%20opposition%E2%80%99s%20effective%20and%20continued%20participation%20in%20Parliament%20is%20a%20litmus%20test%20for%20democracy%2C%20because%20working%20without%20opposition%20is%20easy%2C%20taking%20the%20opposition%20along%20is%20not%20every%20government%E2%80%99s%20cup%20of%20tea!%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYes%2C%20the%20opposition%20must%20also%20conduct%20itself%20honourably%2C%20but%20we%20forget%20that%20opposition%20wields%20no%20power.%20It%20cannot%20compel%20the%20government%20to%20call%20a%20Parliament%20session%2C%20if%20the%20government%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20want%20to.%20It%20cannot%20force%20the%20government%20to%20debate%20a%20particular%20issue%2C%20if%20the%20government%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20want%20to.%20The%20smooth%20functioning%20of%20Parliament%2C%20therefore%2C%20is%20more%20dependent%20on%20the%20benevolence%20of%20the%20government%20than%20the%20disciplined%20conduct%20of%20the%20opposition.%20Left%20with%20no%20choice%2C%20the%20opposition%20protests.%20And%20the%20government%20gains%20from%20it.%20Therefore%2C%20keeping%20the%20opposition%20in%20protest%20mode%20is%20strategically%20beneficial%20for%20the%20government.%20So%2C%20while%20we%20must%20question%20the%20opposition%20MPs%20for%20not%20effectively%20exercising%20a%20check%20on%20the%20government%2C%20we%20must%20question%20the%20government%20more%20aggressively%20for%20abusing%20its%20powers.%20Parliament%20will%20perform%20only%20as%20well%20as%20our%20steadfast%20faith%20in%20its%20place%20in%20our%20democracy.%20If%20we%20abandon%20it%2C%20it%20will%20crumble.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EEnding%20the%20bad%20dream%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20response%20to%20the%20thread%2C%20several%20citizens%20also%20expressed%20despondency%2C%20asking%20whether%20anything%20can%20be%20done%20to%20arrest%20these%20worrying%20trends.%20Indeed%2C%20it%20is%20an%20uphill%20battle%2C%20but%20it%20starts%20with%20accepting%20that%20the%20state%20of%20affairs%20is%20alarming.%20The%20rot%20runs%20deep.%20It%20didn%E2%80%99t%20start%20during%20the%20current%20regime%2C%20but%20it%20has%20certainly%20accelerated%20its%20pace.%20There%20are%20no%20easy%20answers%20on%20how%20to%20remedy%20the%20situation%2C%20but%20no%20solution%20can%20be%20worked%20out%20unless%20citizens%20start%20caring%20about%20the%20health%20of%20their%20institutions.%20The%20government%20will%20only%20respond%20to%20electoral%20compulsions.%20It%20is%20up%20to%20us%20to%20make%20the%20decimation%20of%20Parliament%20into%20a%20political%20issue%20that%20government%20can%E2%80%99t%20afford%20to%20ignore.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EMaansi%20Verma%20is%20a%20lawyer%2C%20public%20policy%20researcher%2C%20and%20Founder%20of%20Maadhyam%20%E2%80%93%20a%20civic%20engagement%20initiative%20bringing%20Parliament%20and%20policy-making%20closer%20to%20people.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706680190000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F31111758%2FGFGx-CPbAAAB7us.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Findian-parliaments-unending-bad-dream%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20biggest%20disservice%20that%20the%20government%20has%20done%20is%20making%20Parliament%20redundant%20in%20people%E2%80%99s%20imaginations.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A6%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Findian-parliaments-unending-bad-dream%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Death%20Penalty%20for%2014%20in%20BJP%20Leader's%20Murder%20Case%3A%20What%20Makes%20the%20Verdict%20Rare%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F31111456%2FUntitled-design-20.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EIn%20a%20rare%20judgment%2C%20the%20Mavelikkara%20Additional%20Sessions%20Court%20in%20Kerala%20has%20sentenced%2014%20workers%20affiliated%20with%20the%20Social%20Democratic%20Party%20of%20India%20(SDPI)%20and%20the%20Popular%20Front%20of%20India%20(PFI)%20to%20death%20for%20the%20murder%20of%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20leader%20%3Cspan%3ERanjith%20Sreenivasan%20in%20Alappuzha%3C%2Fspan%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%20Kerala%20that%20so%20many%20people%20have%20been%20given%20capital%20punishment%20for%20the%20same%20crime%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thenewsminute.com%2Fkerala%2F15-persons-sentenced-to-death-by-alappuzha-court-for-murder-of-bjp-leader-in-kerala%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20News%20Minute%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20also%20imposed%20fines%20and%20rigorous%20imprisonment%20on%20the%20convicted%20individuals%2C%20marking%20a%20rare%20and%20severe%20punishment%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Findia%2Fkerala-death-sentence-pfi-sdpi-men-bjp-ranjith-sreenivasan-murder-9134271%2F%5C%22%3Ereported%3Cem%3E%20Indian%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20sentencing%2C%20delivered%20by%20Mavelikkara%20Additional%20District%20Judge%20V.G.%20Sreedevi%2C%20comes%20770%20days%20after%20Ranjith%20Sreenivasan%20was%20hacked%20to%20death%20on%20December%2019%2C%202021%2C%20in%20front%20of%20his%20wife%2C%20mother%2C%20and%20minor%20daughter.%20Sreenivasan%20was%20a%20BJP%20state%20committee%20member%20and%20OBC%20Morcha%20state%20secretary.%20The%20group%20were%20ostensibly%20avenging%20the%20killing%20of%20SDPI%20leader%20K.S.%20Shan%20the%20night%20before.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20found%20the%20first%2012%20accused%20directly%20involved%20in%20the%20murder%2C%20while%20accused%2013%20to%2015%20were%20deemed%20as%20accomplices.%20The%20prosecution%20established%20murder%20charges%20against%20the%20first%20eight%20accused%2C%20with%20others%20found%20guilty%20of%20criminal%20conspiracy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERanjith%E2%80%99s%20widow%20expressed%20gratitude%20for%20the%20verdict%2C%20saying%20that%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20decision%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Crare%20instance%20of%20justice%20being%20served.%E2%80%9D%20She%20thanked%20the%20prosecution%20and%20the%20police%20for%20their%20%E2%80%9Cunwavering%20support%E2%80%9D%20during%20the%20legal%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20January%2020%2C%20the%20court%20heard%20the%20prosecution%E2%80%99s%20plea%20for%20the%20maximum%20penalty%2C%20describing%20the%20convicts%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Ctrained%20killer%20squad.%E2%80%9D%20The%20trial%20highlighted%20the%20nature%20of%20the%20crime%2C%20categorising%20it%20as%20one%20of%20the%20%E2%80%9Crarest%20of%20the%20rarest%E2%80%9D%20crimes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20convicted%20individuals%20include%20Naizam%2C%20Ajmal%2C%20Anoop%2C%20Muhammed%20Aslam%2C%20Salam%20Ponnad%2C%20Abdul%20Kalam%2C%20Safarudheen%2C%20Munshad%2C%20Jaseeb%20Raja%2C%20Navas%2C%20Shemeer%2C%20Naseer%2C%20Zakeer%20Hussain%2C%20Shaji%20Poovathungal%2C%20and%20Shamnas%20Ashraf.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20murder%20was%20part%20of%20a%20series%20of%20violent%20incidents%20in%20Alappuzha%2C%20involving%20groups%20associated%20with%20both%20the%20SDPI-PFI%20and%20the%20RSS-BJP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20murder%20had%20triggered%20protests%20and%20demonstrations%20by%20activists%20from%20both%20the%20BJP%20and%20SDPI%2C%20prompting%20heightened%20police%20vigilance%20across%20the%20state.%20The%20timing%20of%20the%20murders%2C%20coupled%20with%20the%20alleged%20hit%20list%20found%20on%20the%20third%20accused%E2%80%99s%20mobile%20phone%2C%20adds%20a%20layer%20of%20complexity%20to%20the%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20legal%20proceedings%20exposed%20the%20depth%20of%20animosity%20between%20political%20factions%2C%20leading%20to%20a%20ban%20on%20the%20Popular%20Front%20of%20India%20by%20the%20Centre%20on%20September%2028%2C%202022%2C%20under%20the%20Unlawful%20Activities%20(Prevention)%20Act.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706679965000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F31111456%2FUntitled-design-20.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fpfi-kerala-death-penalty-bjp-leader-murder%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20convicts%20belong%20to%20the%20now-proscribed%20Popular%20Front%20of%20India%20and%20its%20political%20arm%2C%20the%20Social%20De